    <item>
      <title>
        China Was Opposed to Denuclearization of Korean Peninsula
      </title>
      <link>https://www.factopolis.com/person/mike-pompeo/2017-08-14/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 14 Aug 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://www.factopolis.com/person/mike-pompeo/2017-08-14/</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[
        <blockquote>
          We&rsquo;ve seen the Chinese now say for among the first times that they believe the correct answer has to be denuclearized peninsula.
        </blockquote>
        <p>
          <cite>— Mike Pompeo, interview with Fox News&#39; Chris Wallace</cite>
        </p>
        <h4>Claims:</h4>
        <dl>
          
            
            <dt>
              <a href="https://www.factopolis.com/claims/china-was-opposed-to-denuclearization-of-korean-peninsula/">China Was Opposed to Denuclearization of Korean Peninsula</a>
            </dt>
            <dd>
              <h5>The Truth:</h5>

              China has supported it for over a decade.
            </dd>
          
        </dl>
        
          <h4>Fact Checks:</h4>
          <dl>
            
              
              <dt><a href="http://www.FactCheck.org/2017/08/pompeo-distorts-chinas-nuclear-policy/">FactCheck.org</a></dt>
              <dd>
                <blockquote>In fact, China has supported “the verifiable denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula” since at least 2005.</blockquote>
              </dd>
            
          </dl>
        
      ]]></description>
